        {
            "_id": "D5B2HG8wJ5TtWu8c",
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/actions/Passive.webp",
            "name": "Curse of Stone",
            "sort": 800000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "passive"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": null
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>The creature must succeed at a @Check[type:fortitude|dc:21] save or become @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Clumsy]{Clumsy 2} (@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Clumsy]{Clumsy 3} on a critical failure) and gain a +1 status bonus to AC as their skin hardens to stone. The clumsy condition can be temporarily relieved for 24 hours by casting stone to flesh on the cursed creature but can't be removed or reduced by any other means short of removing the curse; during this time, the cursed creature also no longer receives the status bonus to AC.</p>\n<p>@UUID[Compendium.pf2e.bestiary-effects.Item.Effect: Curse of Stone]</p>"
                },
